headline: US Tariff Impact: Prices Surge At Walmart And Target, Employees Say—Some Jumps Top 38%
summary: The tariffs imposed by President Donald Trump are reportedly leading to significant price increases at Walmart Inc. (NYSE:WMT) and Target Corporation (NYSE:TGT) stores across the U.S. What Happened: The Walmart employees have been sharing images on Reddit that depict a sharp rise in prices, with some items seeing a surge of up to 45%. Similar price hikes have been noted at Target as well. For example, a Jurassic World T. Rex toy at Walmart saw its price increase from $39.92 in late April to $55
